snippet.textDisplay:
After decades of research, I have came to a conclusion on the 5th DLC fighter...

Lightning Mcqueen

Now here me out. Sakurai has told us he’ll only be including video game characters. The Cars video game came out on June 6th, 2006. The Cars movie came out on June 9th, 2006. This makes Lightning Mcqueen a video game character. Not to mention Lightning Mcqueen has been in other video games. There has been multiple pixar cars games, as well as disney infinity.

Sakurai wants characters that is fun to play. Lightning Mcqueen could be add very unique elements and attacks to the game. For examples, his specials. His neutral B could be him using his tongue, like how he did in Cars 1. This could do some okay damage, but due to the slobber of the tongue, it’ll make enemies slower for a certain amount of time. This could be a great combo starter.

His Up-B could make use of the jetpack that Mater uses in Cars 2. Now I know that may seem like a stretch, but it could work. Fin Mcmissle or Mater could just let Mcqueen borrow the jetpack.

His Down-B, could be two different attacks depending on the damage Mcqueen received. If Mcqueen is 0-60%, he has the option to explode his tires. This is going to be like in the first movie, where as the race goes on, Mcqueen’s tires blow up one by one. This would do massive damage to the opponent if close enough, yet it’ll make Mcqueen slower as cars can’t drive without tires. Also, since Mcqueen only had four tires, he can only use it four times per stock.Yet if he is above 60%, he’ll transform into his alternate form. ‘Lighting Dragon Mcqueen’, which is a form shown in the Tow Mater stories “Tokyo Mater.” This boosts all of Mcqueen’s damage, speed, and reduces the amount of damage he’ll take from an attack.

His side-B, can be where he rams his body into the opponent really fast, kind of like Sonic’s spin dash.

Anyways, his alt costumes could be from the first three cars movies. As he has many different paint jobs.

Now, his final smash. His final smash would be like Joker’s, where he has to ram into you to hit. The cutscene would be Mcqueen driving away from Frank (the red tractor thing.) Once Frank gets close enough to Mcqueen, he’ll jump out of the way. And guess who would be in front of them, the character hit by the final smash. This would lead to Frank running over the opponent instead. Yet it wouldn’t show the character being cut up and ect, as Smash is for good boys and girls.

In conclusion, Lightning Mcqueen is confirmed for the 5th DLC slot.

snippet.textDisplay:
Am i the only one that wonders why Hubert isn't among the students on the stage ?

Like the other houses follow a pattern : house rep, rep's assistant and 3rd student that represents the house well.
Dimitri and Claude are the house reps and Dedue and Hilda are their respective assistants.
Ingrid's represents the kingdom's knightly ideal marred by politics for the Blue Lions, while Lorenz is Claude's rival and shows how the Alliance is led by a bunch of different people in an uneasy collaboration, but the Black Eagles ?

Edelgard's here, but Hubert is conspicuously missing and we get Petra and Dorothea instead.
Petra's the princess of a foreign country that was conquered by the empire, so she represents its military might by acting as a trophy (as they try to frame her in game). But Dorothea ? What does she represent that's important enough to not put Edelgard's assistant in ?

I'm really curious.
snippet.textOriginal:
Am i the only one that wonders why Hubert isn't among the students on the stage ?

Like the other houses follow a pattern : house rep, rep's assistant and 3rd student that represents the house well.
Dimitri and Claude are the house reps and Dedue and Hilda are their respective assistants.
Ingrid's represents the kingdom's knightly ideal marred by politics for the Blue Lions, while Lorenz is Claude's rival and shows how the Alliance is led by a bunch of different people in an uneasy collaboration, but the Black Eagles ?

Edelgard's here, but Hubert is conspicuously missing and we get Petra and Dorothea instead.
Petra's the princess of a foreign country that was conquered by the empire, so she represents its military might by acting as a trophy (as they try to frame her in game). But Dorothea ? What does she represent that's important enough to not put Edelgard's assistant in ?

I'm really curious.
